'''Edner Brutus''' (1911&ndash;1980) was a [[Haiti]]an politician, [[diplomat]], and historian. He served as [[foreign minister]] of Haiti from 1974 to 1978, and as a historian he is best known for his book ''Révolution dans Saint-Domingue'' (1969). His father, [[Timoléon C. Brutus]], was also a prominent politician and historian.

