{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2012}} {{Infobox UN resolution |number = 543 |organ = SC |date = 29 November |year = 1983 |meeting = 2,502 |code = S/RES/543 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/543(1983) |for = 15 |abstention = 0 |against = 0 |subject = Israel-Syrian Arab Republic |result = Adopted |image = Golan Heights Map.PNG |caption = Golan Heights }}
'''United Nations Security Council resolution 543''', adopted unanimously on 29 November 1983, is a [[legislation]] that considered the report filed by the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] on the subject of the [[United Nations Disengagement Observer Force]]. The Council noted its efforts to establish a durable and just peace in the Middle East, but also expressed its concern over the prevailing state of [[hostility|military tension]] evident in the area.
The resolution decided to call upon the parties concerned to immediately implement [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 338|Resolution 338]] (1973), it renewed the mandate of the Observer Force for another six months until 31 May 1984 and requested that the Secretary-General submit a report on the situation at the end of that period.
==See also== * [[Arab–Israeli conflict]] * [[Golan Heights]] * [[Israel–Syria relations]] * [[List of United Nations Security Council Resolutions 501 to 600]] (1982–1987)
