'''Waltraud Ernst''' (born 1955) is a German professor of the [[history of medicine]] at [[Oxford Brookes University]].<ref name="brookes">{{cite web|url=https://www.brookes.ac.uk/hpc/staff-and-students/academic-staff/?uid=p0075261&op=full|title=Academic staff - Oxford Brookes University|website=brookes.ac.uk|accessdate=11 August 2018}}</ref> She is a specialist in the history of psychiatry.

She attended the [[University of Konstanz]] and obtained her PhD from the [[School of Oriental and African Studies]] in 1987 for a dissertation on psychiatry and mental illness in South Asia, c. 1780 – 1858.

